The United States and the United Kingdom have agreed to establish a new Task Force to support their armed forces personnel, veterans, and their families. This task force will bring together experts from both countries to share best practices and improve support for those in service and their families. The focus of the task force will be on supporting service personnel, veterans, and families, assisting with the transition to civilian life, and providing care and rehabilitation for wounded, injured, and sick personnel. The Undersecretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness and the Minister for Defence Personnel, Welfare, and Veterans will jointly lead the task force.